name: Dr. Sarah Chen
bio: I specialize in helping professionals overcome burnout and work-related stress. With over 10 years of experience, I use evidence-based approaches including CBT and mindfulness techniques to help clients restore work-life balance and find meaning in their careers.

name: Dr. Michael Rodriguez
bio: I work with individuals experiencing anxiety disorders, panic attacks, and phobias. My therapeutic approach combines exposure therapy, cognitive restructuring, and relaxation techniques to help clients manage their anxiety and regain control of their lives.

name: Dr. Emily Thompson
bio: I specialize in trauma-informed care, helping survivors of trauma, PTSD, and complex trauma heal and rebuild their lives. I use EMDR, somatic experiencing, and narrative therapy to support clients in processing traumatic experiences safely.

name: Dr. James Wilson
bio: I focus on couples therapy and relationship counseling, helping partners improve communication, resolve conflicts, and strengthen their bond. I use Gottman Method, Emotionally Focused Therapy, and solution-focused approaches tailored to each couple's unique needs.

name: Dr. Lisa Park
bio: I specialize in treating depression, mood disorders, and helping clients navigate life transitions. My approach integrates interpersonal therapy, behavioral activation, and psychodynamic techniques to address both symptoms and underlying patterns.

name: Dr. Robert Martinez
bio: I work with adults and adolescents with ADHD, helping them develop executive functioning skills, time management strategies, and coping mechanisms. I combine cognitive-behavioral therapy with practical skill-building to support clients in achieving their goals.

name: Dr. Amanda Foster
bio: I specialize in grief counseling and loss, supporting individuals through bereavement, anticipatory grief, and complicated grief. I use person-centered therapy, meaning-making approaches, and expressive arts to help clients process their loss and find a path forward.

name: Dr. David Kim
bio: I focus on sleep disorders, insomnia, and helping clients develop healthy sleep hygiene. I use CBT for insomnia (CBT-I), relaxation training, and behavioral interventions to help clients achieve restful sleep and improve their overall well-being.
